**Nebius Academy** is an educational platform that helps experienced software developers stay at the forefront of technological innovation. We create specialized courses that teach professionals how to effectively use AI tools in real\\-world development workflows.


Our programs are designed to help engineers critically and productively apply artificial intelligence in their professional work, improving code quality, development speed, and overall work efficiency.


Our mission is to provide engineers with access to cutting\\-edge knowledge in AI\\-assisted development and help them become leaders in the new era of programming.

**Who are we looking for?**


We are seeking experienced developers and technical experts for the role of **Instructors** in our AI\\-assisted programming educational program. You can join us on a part\\-time basis, leading interactive live sessions and workshops for professional developers.

**Apply now** — we review applications on an ongoing basis and invite selected candidates for an interview and a test assignment. **If you successfully complete the recruitment** process, we will notify you and either **offer you an open position immediately or reach out to you when a suitable opportunity becomes available.**

**Please submit your resume in English.**



Requirements:  



For our **AI\\-Assisted Programming Instructor** positions, we are looking for experienced software engineers who meet the following criteria:

**Technical Expertise:**

* At least 5 years of professional software development experience (C\\+\\+ experience required for the C\\+\\+ focus position);
* Hands\\-on experience with AI\\-assisted development tools such as Cursor, GitHub Copilot, or similar platforms;
* Understanding of secure coding practices and AI\\-related risks in software development;
* Solid knowledge of system design, testing strategies, and developer tooling;
* Familiarity with command line tools, browser DevTools, and modern development workflows.

**Teaching and Communication Skills:**

* Ability to break down complex technical concepts into clear, actionable, and engaging formats;
* Excellent spoken English and clear technical communication (native or fluent Spanish required for the Spanish\\-speaking position);
* Experience in live facilitation: ability to prompt discussions, handle Q\\&A sessions, and adapt in real\\-time;
* Strong presentation skills and confidence in leading interactive workshops;
* Collaborative and audience\\-oriented mindset.

**Professional Background:**

* Background in developer advocacy, tech leadership, conference speaking, or technical mentoring;
* Experience teaching, coaching, or training developers or engineering teams is highly valued;
* Strong time management and preparation habits;
* Availability of at least 10\\-15 hours per week to dedicate to your students.

**Bonus Points:**

* Experience with remote collaboration tools (Zoom, Miro, Slack, VSCode Live Share, etc.);
* Russian language skills (some of our students speak Russian);
* Active participation in developer communities or open\\-source projects;
* Familiarity with the gaming industry (for the C\\+\\+ focus position).




What you will do:  



We are looking for experienced professionals to fill the **Instructor** role in our AI\\-assisted programming courses.

**Available Positions:**

* **Instructor: Workshops for AI\\-Assisted Programming Course (with C\\+\\+ focus)** — conducting workshops for C\\+\\+ developers from the gaming industry
* **Instructor: AI\\-Assisted Programming (General)** — teaching developers from various backgrounds and specializations
* **Instructor: AI\\-Assisted Programming (Spanish Speaking)** — delivering training in Spanish for Latin American and Spanish audiences

**Your Responsibilities:**

* Conduct interactive live training sessions on AI\\-assisted coding (topics include prompting, code generation, debugging with AI, and productivity workflows);
* Prepare workshop scenarios and training materials in collaboration with our Instructional Designer;
* Communicate with students during Q\\&A sessions and provide guidance;
* Review and incorporate feedback from learners to continuously improve session design;
* Contribute reusable materials (code snippets, prompt libraries, challenge tasks, best practice guides).
* This role requires 10\\-15 hours of availability per week. For the Spanish\\-speaking position, flexibility for Spanish and Latin American time zones is preferred.

 **And most importantly: you will be a source of inspiration for your students!**




What we can offer you:


* **The opportunity to teach while maintaining your primary job**: Share your expertise without leaving your current role.
* **Competitive hourly rate of $40\\-$85 USD** for flexible part\\-time collaboration with significant impact and an amazing team!
* **Remote cooperation with a schedule convenient for both you and the team**: We don't focus on micromanagement.
* **Cross\\-cultural experience**: Become part of an international team and connect with professional developers from diverse backgrounds.
* **Meaningful impact**: Share your knowledge and help experienced engineers advance their skills in AI\\-assisted development.
* **Participation in innovative projects**: Contribute to shaping the future of programming education and AI adoption.
* **Professional growth**: Receive feedback and develop your skills as a technical educator and thought leader.

